<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 1469/95 of 22 June 1995 on measures to be taken with regard to certain beneficiaries of operations financed by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1469/95 meetmete kohta, mis tuleb v&otilde;tta teatavate Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust rahastatavate toimingute abisaajate suhtes 22. juuni 1995 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, at its meetings in June 1993 in Copenhagen and December 1994 in Essen, the European Council stressed the importance of pursuing the campaign against fraud and irregularities affecting the Community budget; whereas there should be a reinforcement of those measures designed to ensure that the Community funds intended for the implementation of the common agricultural policy (CAP) are not granted to persons or companies which do not offer all the guarantees of reliability as to the proper execution of the operations concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: kohtumistel Kopenhaagenis 1993. aasta juunis ning Essenis 1994. aasta detsembris r&otilde;hutas Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu &uuml;henduse eelarvet m&otilde;jutavate eeskirjaeiramiste ja pettuste vastase v&otilde;itluse j&auml;tkamise t&auml;htsust; tuleks tugevdada meetmeid, mis on kavandatud selle tagamiseks, et &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rakendamiseks kavandatud &uuml;henduse vahendeid ei anta isikutele v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingutele, kes ei t&auml;ida asjakohaste toimingute n&otilde;uetekohaseks l&auml;biviimiseks k&otilde;iki usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsuse n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 8 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 of 21 April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy (4), lays down, in particular, that Member States are under an obligation to take all the measures necessary to ensure that transactions financed by the Fund are actually carried out and properly executed, and to prevent and follow up irregularities; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (&uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamise kohta (4)) artiklis 8 s&auml;testatakse eelk&otilde;ige, et liikmesriigid on kohustatud v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed fondi rahastatud tehingute tegeliku ja &otilde;igesti toimumise tagamiseks ning eeskirjade eiramiste v&auml;ltimiseks ja edasiseks uurimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Council Regulation (EEC) No 595/91 of 4 March 1991 concerning irregularities and the recovery of sums wrongly paid in connection with the financing of the common agricultural policy and the organization of an information system in this field and repealing Regulation (EEC) No 283/72 (5), provides, among other things, for the Member States regularly to inform the Commission of cases of irregularities and judicial or administrative procedures sanctioning persons who have committed irregularities, in order to acquire systematic knowledge of the nature of the fraudulent practices and to recover sums wrongly paid; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 4. m&auml;rtsi 1991. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 595/91 eeskirjade eiramise ja valesti makstud summade sissen&otilde;udmise kohta &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamisel, infos&uuml;steemi loomise kohta selles valdkonnas ning m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 283/72 (5) kehtetukstunnistamise kohta s&auml;testatakse muuhulgas, et liikmesriigid teavitavad korrap&auml;raselt komisjoni eeskirjade eiramistest ja kohtu- v&otilde;i haldusmenetlustest, millega rakendatakse sanktsioone eeskirju eiranud isikute suhtes, eesm&auml;rgiga saada j&auml;rjekindlat teavet pettuste laadi kohta ning et n&otilde;uda sisse valesti makstud summad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas these provisions need to be supplemented by a Community system allowing all the national authorities to identify, in connection with tendering procedures, grant of export refunds or sales at reduced prices of intervention products, operators who have deliberately or as a result of serious negligence committed an irregularity prejudicial to Community funds or who are suspected on solid grounds of having done so; whereas, on that basis, there must be determined, in the light of the seriousness of the offence and depending on whether it has been established or suspected, a series of varied measures ranging from reinforced controls to the exclusion of the operators concerned from taking part in operations to be determined when their fraudulent actions are established; </inglise>
<eesti> neid s&auml;tteid on vaja t&auml;iendada &uuml;henduse s&uuml;steemiga, mis v&otilde;imaldab k&otilde;ikidel siseriiklikel ametiasutustel pakkumismenetluste, eksporditoetuste maksmise v&otilde;i alandatud hindadega sekkumiskaupade m&uuml;&uuml;gi k&auml;igus kindlaks teha ettev&otilde;tjad, kes on tahtlikult v&otilde;i raske hooletuse tulemusel eeskirju eiranud ja sellega &uuml;hendusele rahalist kahju p&otilde;hjustanud v&otilde;i keda selles p&otilde;hjendatult kahtlustakse; selle alusel tuleb s&uuml;&uuml;teo raskust arvestades ja olenevalt sellest, kas see on tuvastatud v&otilde;i oletatav, m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks mitmesugused meetmed alates tugevdatud kontrollist kuni asjaomaste ettev&otilde;tjate v&auml;listamiseni teatavatest tegevustest, kui nende pettuslik tegevus on tuvastatud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to provide operators with a maximum of guarantees, it would be advisable to adopt the essential features of the corresponding provisions of Regulation (EEC) No 595/91, in particular with regard to the observance of confidentiality and professional secrecy and the national rules relating to criminal proceedings; whereas, with regard to data protection, the relevant provisions laid down for that purpose in the rules on mutual assistance in customs and agricultural matters may be applied; </inglise>
<eesti> ettev&otilde;tjatele maksimaalse tagatise andmiseks oleks soovitatav v&otilde;tta vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 595/91 vastavate s&auml;tete olulised osad, eelk&otilde;ige seoses konfidentsiaalsuse ja ametisaladuse j&auml;rgimise ning kriminaalmenetlust puudutavate siseriiklike eeskirjadega; andmekaitse suhtes v&otilde;ib kohaldada selleks etten&auml;htud asjakohaseid s&auml;tteid tolli- ja p&otilde;llumajandusk&uuml;simusi k&auml;sitlevates vastastikuse abi eeskirjades; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this system must be supplementary to the specific provisions already existing or to be adopted in the future under the CAP with a view to preventing irregularities, in particular those provisions relating to controls and sanctions established by the Commission by virtue of its powers confirmed by the Court of Justice; </inglise>
<eesti> see s&uuml;steem peab t&auml;iendama olemasolevaid v&otilde;i tulevikus &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika raames vastuv&otilde;etavaid eeskirjade eiramise v&auml;ltimiseks kavandatavaid konkreetseid s&auml;tteid, eelk&otilde;ige s&auml;tteid, mis k&auml;sitlevad Euroopa Kohtu kinnitatud volituste alusel komisjoni poolt kehtestavaid kontrollimisi ja sanktsioone; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, furthermore, as part of an across-the-board campaign against fraud, on 7 July 1994 the Commission submitted a proposal for a Regulation (EC, Euratom) on protection of the Community's financial interests (1), whereas, on the adoption of that Regulation by the Council, the common set of legal rules enacted by it for all areas of Community policy will apply to the measures introduced by this Regulation; whereas, until that Regulation is adopted, provision should be made for the detailed rules for the application of this Regulation temporarily to include similar rules, in particular as regards the definition of the irregularities involved, </inglise>
<eesti> lisaks sellele esitas komisjon &uuml;ldise pettusevastase v&otilde;itluse osana 7. juulil 1994 ettepaneku &uuml;henduse finantshuvide kaitset k&auml;sitleva m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;, EURATOM) (6) kohta; kui n&otilde;ukogu on k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse vastu v&otilde;tnud, kohaldatakse sellega k&otilde;ikidel &uuml;henduse poliitikaga h&otilde;lmatud aladel kehtestatud &uuml;htseid &otilde;igusnorme k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud meetmete suhtes; k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse vastuv&otilde;tmiseni tuleks s&auml;testada, et k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad sisaldavad ajutiselt sarnaseid eeskirju, eelk&otilde;ige asjassepuutuvate eeskirjaeiramiste m&auml;&auml;ratluste kohta, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A Community system is hereby established for the purpose of identifying and making known as rapidly as possible to all the competent authorities of the Member States and the Commission operators presenting, on the grounds of experience acquired with them as regards the proper execution of their previous obligations, a risk of non-reliability in connection with tendering procedures, export refunds and sales at reduced prices or intervention products, financed by the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga kehtestatakse &uuml;henduse s&uuml;steem, mille eesm&auml;rk on v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti tuvastada ning liikmesriikide p&auml;devatele asutustele ja komisjonile teatada ettev&otilde;tjad, kes varasemate kohustuste n&otilde;uetekohase t&auml;itmisega seoses saadud kogemuste p&otilde;hjal v&otilde;ivad osutuda ebausaldusv&auml;&auml;rseks EAGGFi tagatisrahastu rahastatavate pakkumismenetluste, eksporditoetuste maksmise v&otilde;i sekkumistoodete alandatud hindadega m&uuml;&uuml;gi puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation, 'operators presenting a risk of non-reliability' means operators, whether natural or legal persons, who: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamisel t&auml;hendavad "ebausaldusv&auml;&auml;rseks osutuda v&otilde;ivad ettev&otilde;tjad" selliseid f&uuml;&uuml;silisest v&otilde;i juriidilisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjaid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) according to a final decision of an administrative or judicial authority, have deliberately or through serious negligence committed an irregularity in respect of relevant Community provisions and have unjustly benefited from a financial advantage or attempted to benefit therefrom; </inglise>
<eesti> a) kes haldusasutuse v&otilde;i kohtu l&otilde;pliku otsuse j&auml;rgi on tahtlikult v&otilde;i raske hooletuse t&otilde;ttu eiranud asjakohaseid &uuml;henduse s&auml;tteid ning kes on alusetult saanud v&otilde;i &uuml;ritanud saada kasu finantssoodustusest; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) have been the subject, in this respect, on the basis of established facts, of a preliminary administrative or judicial report by the competent authorities of the Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> b) kelle kohta on liikmesriigi p&auml;devad haldusasutused v&otilde;i kohtud esitanud sellekohase eelraporti tuvastatud faktide alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Pending the entry into force of horizontal provisions defining irregularities, the conduct referred to in paragraph 2 (a) shall be defined in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 5. </inglise>
<eesti> Enne eeskirjade eiramisi m&auml;&auml;ratlevate &uuml;ldiste &otilde;igusaktide j&otilde;ustumist m&auml;&auml;ratletakse l&otilde;ike 2 punktis a osutatud teguviis artiklis 5 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The identification procedures and rules relating to notification shall be implemented on the initiative of the Member State in which the risk of the operator's non-reliability is identified. </inglise>
<eesti> Tuvastamiskorda ja teatamise eeskirju rakendatakse selle liikmesriigi algatusel, kus ettev&otilde;tja ebausaldusv&auml;&auml;ruse oht tuvastati. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a Member State fails to fulfil its obligation under paragraph 1 the Commission shall, within the framework of the existing legal provisions, ensure that the identification and notification system is implemented by the Member State concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik ei t&auml;ida l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud kohustust, tagab komisjon olemasolevate &otilde;iguss&auml;tetega, et asjaomane liikmesriik rakendab tuvastamise ja teatamise s&uuml;steemi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take the following measures to deal with the operators referred to in Article 1 (2) (a): </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis a osutatud ettev&otilde;tjate suhtes v&otilde;tab liikmesriik j&auml;rgmised meetmed: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) reinforced checking of all operations performed by the operator, and/or (b) suspension, going as far as an administrative determination of the existence of an irregularity or of the absence of an irregularity, of payment of amounts relating to current operations, to be determined, and, where appropriate, of release of the guarantee relating thereto, and/or (c) their exclusion for a period of time from operations to be determined. </inglise>
<eesti> a) tugevdatud kontroll ettev&otilde;tja k&otilde;igi toimingute &uuml;le ja/v&otilde;i b) kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud jooksvate toimingutega seotud maksete peatamine ja vajaduse korral sellekohaste tagatiste vabastamine, kuni eeskirjade eiramine v&otilde;i selle puudumine on halduskorras tuvastatud, ja/v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> The measures referred to under points (b) and (c) shall be determined by the competent authorities of the Member State in accordance with criteria laid down in accordance with the procedure provided for in Article 5, having due regard to the risk of further irregularities that may be committed by the operator. </inglise>
<eesti> c) ettev&otilde;tja v&auml;listamine kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud toimingutest teatavaks ajaks. Punktides b ja c osutatud meetmed m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus vastavalt artiklis 5 s&auml;testatud korras etten&auml;htud kriteeriumidele, v&otilde;ttes kohe arvesse edasist eeskirjade eiramise ohtu ettev&otilde;tja poolt. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall be adopted after any formalities relating thereto laid down in the laws of the Member States have been completed. </inglise>
<eesti> Meetmed v&otilde;etakse vastu p&auml;rast liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud asjakohaste formaalsuste t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards the operators referred to in Article 1 (2) (b), only the measures set out in paragraph 1 points (a) and (b) shall apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis b osutatud ettev&otilde;tjate suhtes kohaldatakse &uuml;ksnes l&otilde;ike 1 punkte a ja b. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where, under a tendering procedure, the Commission itself awards a contract, it shall, as appropriate, take or propose to the Member State, one or more of the measures set out in paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui pakkumismenetluse k&auml;igus s&otilde;lmib komisjon ise lepingu, v&otilde;tab ta vastavalt vajadusele &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitu l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud meetmetest v&otilde;i teeb liikmesriigile sellekohase ettepaneku. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The measures referred to in Article 3 shall comply with the following principles, in accordance with the national law of the Member State: </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 3 osutatud meetmed peavad vastama j&auml;rgmistele liikmesriigi &otilde;igusaktidega koosk&otilde;las olevatele p&otilde;him&otilde;tetele: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) a prior hearing and right of appeal by the operator concerned in respect of the measures referred to in Article 3 (1) (c) and, where appropriate, (b); </inglise>
<eesti> a) artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis c ja vajaduse korral punktis b osutatud meetmete puhul asjaomase ettev&otilde;tja eelnev &auml;rakuulamine ning tema edasikaebe &otilde;igus; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) proportionality between the irregularity committed or suspected and one or other of the measures referred to in Article 3 (1), subject to the provisions to be established in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 5; </inglise>
<eesti> b) proportsionaalsus toimunud v&otilde;i kahtlustatava eeskirjade eiramise ja m&otilde;ne artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud meetme vahel vastavalt l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud korras kehtestatavatele s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) non-discrimination between operators. </inglise>
<eesti> c) ettev&otilde;tjate vaheline mittediskrimineerimise. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States and the Commission shall take all necessary precautions to ensure that the information which they exchange pursuant to this Regulation remains confidential. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid ja komisjon v&otilde;tavad vajalikke ettevaatusabin&otilde;usid, et tagada k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt vahetatud teabe konfidentsiaalsus. </eesti>
<inglise> Such information may not, in particular, be sent to persons other than those in the Member States or within the Community institutions whose duties require that they have access to it, unless the Member State supplying it has expressly so agreed. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda teavet ei tohi edastada muudele isikutele kui neile, kelle ameti&uuml;lesanded liikmesriigis v&otilde;i &uuml;henduse institutsioonides n&otilde;uavad juurdep&auml;&auml;su nimetatud teabele, v&auml;lja arvatud kui teabe esitanud liikmesriigiga on teisiti kokku lepitud. </eesti>
<inglise> Information communicated or acquired in any form under this Regulation shall be covered by professional confidentiality and protected in the same way as similar information is protected by the national legislation of the Member State that received it and by the corresponding provisions applicable to the Community institutions. </inglise>
<eesti> Kogu k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel mis tahes vormis edastatud v&otilde;i saadud teavet k&auml;sitletakse ametisaladusena ja seda kaitstakse nagu muud samalaadset informatsiooni teabe vastuv&otilde;tnud liikmesriigi siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide ja vastavate &uuml;henduse institutsioonide suhtes kehtivate s&auml;tetega. </eesti>
<inglise> In addition, that information may not be used for purposes other than those provided for in this Regulation unless the authorities providing it have expressly agreed and provided that the provisions in force in the Member State in which the authority that has received it is located do not prohibit such communication or use. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks sellele ei tohi seda teavet kasutada ka &uuml;helgi muul kui k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkidel, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui teabe esitanud asutused on selleks andnud selgelt v&auml;ljendatud n&otilde;usoleku, ning tingimusel, et selles liikmesriigis kehtivad s&auml;tted, kus teabe vastu v&otilde;tnud asutus paikneb, ei keela sellist edastamist v&otilde;i kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise> As regards data protection, the relevant provisions laid down in the rules on mutual assistance in customs and agricultural matters shall apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Andmekaitse suhtes kohaldatakse selleks etten&auml;htud asjakohaseid s&auml;tteid tolli- ja p&otilde;llumajandusk&uuml;simusi k&auml;sitlevates vastastikuse abi eeskirjades. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of this Regulation shall not affect the application in the Member States of rules governing criminal proceedings and mutual assistance in criminal matters between Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tted ei m&otilde;juta kriminaalmenetlust ning liikmesriikide poolt kriminaalasjades antavat vastastikust abi k&auml;sitlevate eeskirjade kohaldamist liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall not prevent the use, in the context of judicial proceedings or of proceedings brought subsequently for non-compliance with agricultural regulations, of information obtained pursuant to this Regulation; in the latter case the competent authority of the Member State which provided such information shall be notified of such use. </inglise>
<eesti> Need ei v&auml;lista k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt hangitud teabe kasutamist kohtumenetluses v&otilde;i menetluses, mis on algatatud hiljem p&otilde;llumajandusm&auml;&auml;ruste rikkumise suhtes; viimasel juhul teavitatakse teabe esitanud p&auml;devat asutust sellisest kasutamisest. </eesti>
<inglise> However, Member States shall take the administrative measures necessary to ensure that the provisions of the first subparagraph are applied in such a way as not to hinder the effective application of this Regulation as regards the operators referred to in Article 1 (2) (b). </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad siiski vajalikud haldusmeetmed, et tagada esimeses l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatud meetmete kohaldamine viisil, mis ei takista k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse t&otilde;husat kohaldamist artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 2 punktis b osutatud ettev&otilde;tjate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> If national laws provide for the confidentiality of judicial investigations, communication of information as provided for in this Regulation shall be subject to authorization by the competent judicial authority. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui siseriiklikud &otilde;igusaktid n&auml;evad ette kohtuliku uurimise konfidentsiaalsust, toimub k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud teabe edastamine p&auml;deva kohtu loal. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent administrative authority shall secure such authorization at the earliest opportunity. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;dev haldusasutus tagab sellise loa saamise esimesel v&otilde;imalusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Detailed rules for the application of this Regulation shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 13 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad v&otilde;etakse vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artikliga 13 ette n&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall concern, among other things: </inglise>
<eesti> Need k&auml;sitlevad muuhulgas j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> - the notifications to be made by the Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> - liikmesriikide antav teave; </eesti>
<inglise> - the nature of the links between different natural or legal persons which may result in their being regarded as operators within the meaning of this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> - eri f&uuml;&uuml;siliste ja juriidiliste isikute vaheliste seoste laad, mille alusel v&otilde;ib neid pidada ettev&otilde;tjateks k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> - the conditions under which operators may avoid the suspension of payments as referred to in Article 3 (1) (b) by lodging a security. </inglise>
<eesti> - tingimused, mille alusel ettev&otilde;tjad v&otilde;ivad tagatise esitamisega v&auml;ltida artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis b osutatud maksete peatamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be supplementary to the specific provisions under the CAP. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus t&auml;iendab &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika eris&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall present to the European Parliament and the Council by 6 July 1997 a report on the implementation of this Regulation and, in the light of experience gained, shall propose amendments that may be needed to the arrangements introduced by this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon esitab 6. juuliks 1997 Euroopa Parlamendile ja n&otilde;ukogule aruande k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse rakendamise kohta ja teeb saadud kogemuste p&otilde;hjal vajalikud ettepanekud k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud korra muutmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
